00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.357
- I hope you're having
an amazing day today.

00:00:02.357 --> 00:00:04.603
It's Mark Weins here in Bangkok, Thailand

00:00:04.603 --> 00:00:06.020
and I'm going to share with you

00:00:06.020 --> 00:00:09.520
an authentic Thai recipe for a chili curry

00:00:10.578 --> 00:00:12.066
made with pork ribs

00:00:12.066 --> 00:00:14.573
that has some massive flavor.

00:00:14.573 --> 00:00:17.156
(upbeat music)

00:00:19.877 --> 00:00:22.926
In Thai, this dish is called
gaeng khua prik seekong moo

00:00:22.926 --> 00:00:24.542
and it's a southern Thai dish.

00:00:24.542 --> 00:00:26.878
It is a dried chili curry.

00:00:26.878 --> 00:00:28.767
We're gonna first pound up the curry paste

00:00:28.767 --> 00:00:31.782
then we're gonna cook it
together with pork ribs.

00:00:31.782 --> 00:00:34.398
You can use pork ribs
or you can use chicken,

00:00:34.398 --> 00:00:36.203
you can use any other meat of choice.

00:00:36.203 --> 00:00:37.986
But this is an amazing dish,

00:00:37.986 --> 00:00:39.137
it has so much flavor,

00:00:39.137 --> 00:00:41.933
and it's a dish my
mother-in-law loves to make.

00:00:41.933 --> 00:00:45.784
So I am excited to share the
recipe with you here today.

00:00:45.784 --> 00:00:49.701
(speaking in foreign language)

00:00:51.689 --> 00:00:53.552
So the first step is gonna be to pound up

00:00:53.552 --> 00:00:57.275
all of the ingredients
for the curry paste.

00:00:57.275 --> 00:01:00.653
These are Thai bird's eye chilies dried.

00:01:00.653 --> 00:01:03.319
(speaks in foreign language)

00:01:03.319 --> 00:01:05.198
first, the thing you gotta
do with dried chilies,

00:01:05.198 --> 00:01:07.086
take a big handful

00:01:07.086 --> 00:01:09.246
and just soak them in water.

00:01:09.246 --> 00:01:12.839
(speaking in foreign language)

00:01:12.839 --> 00:01:16.577
Oh, okay, until they get kinda soft.

00:01:16.577 --> 00:01:19.645
Kinda like rehydrating them.

00:01:19.645 --> 00:01:22.999
You wanna soak those dried
chilies for about five minutes

00:01:22.999 --> 00:01:24.795
until they get nice and soft

00:01:24.795 --> 00:01:26.313
and that way they'll be easier to pound.

00:01:26.313 --> 00:01:29.149
And now just to prepare the
garlic and some shallots.

00:01:29.149 --> 00:01:31.503
And so you just peel off the skin

00:01:31.503 --> 00:01:33.183
and then we're gonna
pound that all together.

00:01:33.183 --> 00:01:35.359
And next step, this is
fresh turmeric root.

00:01:35.359 --> 00:01:37.841
And she's just very
roughly peeling the skin

00:01:37.841 --> 00:01:39.346
of the turmeric and you can see

00:01:39.346 --> 00:01:41.397
just that beautiful
orange color below there,

00:01:41.397 --> 00:01:42.944
oh I love turmeric.

00:01:42.944 --> 00:01:44.091
For southern Thai food,

00:01:44.091 --> 00:01:46.248
there's turmeric in almost every dish.

00:01:46.248 --> 00:01:48.415
Next step for lemon grass.

00:01:49.446 --> 00:01:52.073
She's just slicing it thinly
so that we can pound it easier

00:01:52.073 --> 00:01:55.175
when we're making the curry paste.

00:01:55.175 --> 00:01:58.008
This in Thai is called rak phakchi

00:01:58.854 --> 00:02:00.968
and this is coriander roots.

00:02:00.968 --> 00:02:03.315
Again just slice them up.

00:02:03.315 --> 00:02:05.065
This is old galangal.

00:02:06.444 --> 00:02:10.284
So you can see how it's
even tough to cut it,

00:02:10.284 --> 00:02:11.596
it's so hard.

00:02:11.596 --> 00:02:13.416
But that's gonna provide
some awesome flavor

00:02:13.416 --> 00:02:15.166
for this curry paste.

00:02:18.871 --> 00:02:23.092
Okay next up, we just
have some black pepper.

00:02:23.092 --> 00:02:24.190
And we have two more dry spices,

00:02:24.190 --> 00:02:26.357
coriander seeds and cumin.

00:02:28.136 --> 00:02:31.490
And she's just gonna
quickly head over to the wok

00:02:31.490 --> 00:02:34.203
and give them a dry fry
for about 30 seconds

00:02:34.203 --> 00:02:36.085
just to make them nice and fragrant.

00:02:36.085 --> 00:02:38.752
So in goes the cumin and in goes

00:02:40.076 --> 00:02:43.576
about a teaspoon or so of coriander seeds.

00:02:51.311 --> 00:02:54.028
Oh, that aroma of spice

00:02:54.028 --> 00:02:55.521
is a beautiful thing.

00:02:55.521 --> 00:02:58.002
The next thing you've gotta
do is the really fun part,

00:02:58.002 --> 00:02:59.513
to pound up the curry paste.

00:02:59.513 --> 00:03:01.569
She said that the chilies
are nice and soft.

00:03:01.569 --> 00:03:04.575
They've been sitting in the
water for about five minutes

00:03:04.575 --> 00:03:06.155
while we prepared all
the other ingredients.

00:03:06.155 --> 00:03:08.134
And then you can set them
on the plate as well.

00:03:08.134 --> 00:03:12.275
That's like breathing fresh
new life into chilies.

00:03:12.275 --> 00:03:13.247
We're just gonna pound up everything,

00:03:13.247 --> 00:03:15.140
but she said to first

00:03:15.140 --> 00:03:18.042
add like kind of half of the ingredients.

00:03:18.042 --> 00:03:20.100
I think the mortar is not quite big enough

00:03:20.100 --> 00:03:21.144
to fit everything.

00:03:21.144 --> 00:03:24.311
So then sprinkle with a spoon of salt.

00:03:29.445 --> 00:03:30.900
And at this stage,

00:03:30.900 --> 00:03:33.914
it's time to ground and pound.

00:03:33.914 --> 00:03:35.098
Take the mortar to the ground.

00:03:35.098 --> 00:03:37.679
You've gotta take it on the ground or

00:03:37.679 --> 00:03:40.494
yeah you gotta be on a non-bouncy surface.

00:03:40.494 --> 00:03:43.691
This bamboo table chair is way too bouncy.

00:03:43.691 --> 00:03:46.024
Alright, let's get pounding.

00:03:48.944 --> 00:03:50.013
You're gonna have to pound this up

00:03:50.013 --> 00:03:51.548
for probably about an hour,

00:03:51.548 --> 00:03:54.056
maybe 45 minutes if you're really good.

00:03:54.056 --> 00:03:56.938
But you will definitely get a workout

00:03:56.938 --> 00:03:59.182
and break a sweat when
you're pounding this.

00:03:59.182 --> 00:04:01.765
(upbeat music)

00:04:06.209 --> 00:04:07.701
Okay now we can go ahead and toss in

00:04:07.701 --> 00:04:10.872
the rest of those dry chilies.

00:04:10.872 --> 00:04:14.122
There's a little bit of spice left too.

00:04:15.487 --> 00:04:16.792
Alright.

00:04:16.792 --> 00:04:18.727
And then just keep on pounding.

00:04:18.727 --> 00:04:21.310
(upbeat music)

00:04:22.820 --> 00:04:25.138
I have been pounding for about 30 minutes.

00:04:25.138 --> 00:04:27.869
We've got a really nice paste,

00:04:27.869 --> 00:04:30.475
look at the consistency and color of that.

00:04:30.475 --> 00:04:32.059
And I got the okay from my mother-in-law

00:04:32.059 --> 00:04:34.660
to make the last step in
this curry paste recipe.

00:04:34.660 --> 00:04:37.776
And that is to add the shrimp paste.

00:04:37.776 --> 00:04:39.944
Oh, that's sticky shrimp paste.

00:04:39.944 --> 00:04:44.209
Alright, there we go and then
you can just sort of mash

00:04:44.209 --> 00:04:47.841
and push the shrimp paste to distribute it

00:04:47.841 --> 00:04:51.040
